Brazil Gourmet is a blessing to brazilians in the area. They offer a variety of Brazilian products but the BEST part is the food! You can eat in or order for parties. I used their services for my daughter's birthday and I was delighted by the service, quality and professionalism. THE SALGADINHOS WERE TO DIE FOR! Late last month I called few hours before an event and again I was not dissappointed. They accommodated the last minutw order and again the treats were a hit. It's true that prices can be a bit high but I know it costs to import products. I am very pleased with Brazil Gourmet and I hope they will be here to stay.
For half of the price of fogo de Chao you can still get all you can eat meat here. The selection is smaller of course but the still have picana, the king of all cuts.

Love this place and have been back several times to pick up both staples and specialties and indulge in a bit of Brazil nostalgia. Having been to Sao Paulo I can say this place super legit (and decent prices too). Flours, grains, cheeses, coffee, frozen goods, snacks, the list goes on. All imported and high quality. Staff is super friendly too!

Delicious and affordable. A gem of the neighborhood. Small and very personal feeling, you can tell everything is made to order and it's all amazing. The cheese bread is outstanding. This place is so cute! I love the feel and vibe. The staff is wonderfully friendly and welcoming. My Brazilian best friend says he feels closer to home here. I'll definitely be back. Also, the Brazilian coffee is delicious and as strong as it should be.
Great prepared food that reminds me of home-cooked in Brasil, friendly staff, spotless shop, wonderful Brazilian groceries, very reasonable prices! We will return!!

Amazing place! They have a variety of products from Brazil at reasonable prices. They also sell little snacks (salgadinhos) and delicious coffee. The two young guys (staff) who were there that day were extremely nice and friendly. I will definitely go back soon for more snacks :D Obrigada!
(Translated by Google) Finally something with a taste of Brazil in Baltimore, I will for sure be going back!  (Original) Finalmente algo com gosto do Brasil em Baltimore, eu com certeza vou voltar!

The coffee is excellent. We ordered several small appetizers which were delicious. I particularly recommend the salgados (various types— we had the espinas which are filled with chicken) and coxinhas (pastry filled with chicken). For dessert, try the brigadeiros — chocolate filled with chocolate flavored condensed milk. Small store on premises for Brazilian goods.
